        Searches n       Expand Searches menu  n n                  Search Process n                  n n                  Search Resources n                  n n                  Frequently Asked Questions n                 Eyebrow menu OAE Policies Trainings Contact Us UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map Breadcrumbs Office for Access and Equity Resources Gender Inclusive Resources Lactation Rooms In accordance with Section      of the Affordable Care Act  an employer shall provide reasonable break time to an employee who needs to express breast milk for her infant child for up to one year after the child s birth  An employer shall provide a private space  other than a bathroom  where an employee can express her milk on an as needed basis Below is a list of designated lactation rooms at UIC  There are many more areas that are informally designated as lactation rooms  Representatives in the colleges and administrative units accommodate the needs of nursing mothers at a decentralized level  therefore  please check your department representative to secure space East Side of Campus West Side of Campus These rooms are reserved for use only by the students  faculty and staff of that college Public Lactation Rooms Public Lactation Rooms Compensation Nursing mothers shall be paid for break time needed for nursing or expressing milk  The break time may run concurrently with any break time already established  Nursing mothers are also entitled to a reasonable number of additional paid breaks to allow to them to nurse or express milk  Departments shall provide reasonable break time as needed by the employee unless doing so would create an undue hardship as defined by the Illinois Human Rights Act  Supervisors are asked to contact their university or system human resources office before denying an employee a paid break for expressing milk based on the undue hardship exclusion   University of Illinois System Human Resource Services  University of Illinois System Human Resource Services